  <section class="content-section">
    <h2 class="section-title">FIDE Chess Rules</h2>
    <div class="text-content">
      <p>Chessy.gg follows the official FIDE rules. Here are the most important concepts:</p>
      <div class="rules-grid">
        <div class="rule-card">
          <h3>Piece Movement</h3>
          <p>Pawns move forward, rooks move straight, bishops diagonally, knights jump in "L" shapes, and queens can move in all directions. Kings move one square.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rule-card">
          <h3>Castling</h3>
          <p>Move the king two squares toward a rook and the rook to the other side. Ensure no pieces are between them and neither has moved before.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rule-card">
          <h3>Check & Checkmate</h3>
          <p>A check is when the king is under attack. Checkmate ends the game when the king cannot escape.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rule-card">
          <h3>En Passant</h3>
          <p>A special pawn capture that occurs when a pawn moves two squares forward from its starting position and lands beside an opponent's pawn.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <h2 class="section-title">Elo Rating System</h2>
    <div class="text-content">
      <p>Chessy.gg uses the Elo rating system to evaluate player performance. Here's how it works:</p>
      <ul class="elo-list">
        <li>Your Elo increases when you win and decreases when you lose, depending on your opponent's rating.</li>
        <li>Winning against a higher-rated opponent results in a bigger rating boost.</li>
        <li>Drawing or losing to a lower-rated opponent has a more significant impact on your rating.</li>
        <li>Consistency and playing stronger opponents will help you climb the leaderboard.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Learn more about the Elo system in our <a href="/elo-explained" class="highlight">detailed guide</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <h2 class="section-title">Advanced Chess Tips</h2>
    <div class="text-content">
      <p>Once you're familiar with the basics, take your chess skills to the next level with these tips:</p>
      <ul class="tips-list">
        <li>Control the center of the board early in the game.</li>
        <li>Keep your king safe by castling early.</li>
        <li>Think a few moves ahead and anticipate your opponent's plans.</li>
        <li>Use all your pieces to create a coordinated attack.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
  
